addEntry(uint256,string,string,string).details: Add an entry to a specific track.  The entry is attached to a track as stored data on-chain. However, the  actual data belonging to the entry is emitted as an event.

returns._0: the id of the new entry.

addTrack(string,string).details: Add a track. The track is stored as data on-chain.

params._desc: a brief description of what the track is about.

returns._0: the trackId of the new track.

banUser(address,bool).details: Ban a user from participation.   This function is only availble to the contract owner.

params.addr: , address of the user to block
params.banned: , true to ban, false to unban.

blockTrack(uint256).details: Set a specific track to the 'Blocked' state.

closeTrack(uint256).details: Set a specific track to the 'Closed' state.

constructor.details: Create the new contract.  The default is to have tracks open with cooldowns enabled.

disableAllTracks(bool).details: Set all existing tracks to the 'Blocked' state.

params.enable: true to block, false to unblock.

disableAllVoting(bool).details: Set all voting to the 'Blocked' state.

params.enable: , true to block, false to unblock.

donateToOwner(uint256).details: Set the percentage of transaction fees to add to donations. 	Donations are restricted to (0, 1] ether.

donateToTrackOwner(uint256,uint256).details: Set the percentage of transaction fees to add to donations. 	Donations are restricted to (0, 1] ether.

params._trackId: id of the track to donate to

enableCooldowns(bool).details: Enable or disable the use of cooldowns.  Cooldown allows automation blocking to balance throughput.

params.enable: A bool set to true to enable cooldowns, false to disable.

getEntriesForTrack(uint256).details: Get all the entries attached to a specific track

returns._0: all the Entry ids attached to the track

getTrackState(uint256).details: Get the state of a track as a string key.

returns._0: array of all tracks by object

isSenderInEntryCreationCooldown().details: Check if a user is in a cooldown period for entry creation.  Cooldown allows automation blocking to balance throughput.

returns._0: true if user is in cooldown, false otherwise.

isSenderInTrackCreationCooldown().details: Check if a user is in a cooldown period for track creation.  Cooldown allows automation blocking to balance throughput.

returns._0: true if user is in cooldown, false otherwise.

isSenderInVotingCooldown(uint256).details: Check if a user is in a cooldown period for voting.  Cooldown allows automation blocking to balance throughput.

returns._0: true if user is in cooldown, false otherwise.

isTrackBlocked(uint256).details: Check a specific track is in the 'Blocked' state.

isTrackClosed(uint256).details: Check a specific track is in the 'Open' state.

isTrackOpen(uint256).details: Check a specific track is in the 'Open' state.

isUserBanned(address).details: CHeck if a user is bannedfrom participation.

params.addr: , address of the user to block

openTrack(uint256).details: Set a specific track to the 'Open' state.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setMaxTrackCount(uint256).details: set the maximum amount of tracks to iterate through

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unblockTrack(uint256).details: Unblock a specific track by settings to the 'Closed' state.

vote(uint256).details: Vote for an entry.   Voting emits an event. It also sets a number of variables to follow  users voting patterns so that multiple voting and cooldowns can be   monitored.

withdraw().details: Withdraw the donations to the senders address (if allowed) 	Donations are restricted to (0, 1] ether.

devdoc.title: The Tracks contract enables the storage of collections of  text information with voting enabled on each memeber of the collection through emitting events.
